refentry.refsect1:
&reftitle.description;
public CollectionModifymysql_xdevapi\CollectionModify::arrayAppend stringcollection_field stringexpression_or_literal
Add an element to one of the fields of a document, multiple elements of a field are reppresented as an array. the arrayAppend differs from arrayIndert in the way that this function will always append the new element at the end of the array, while arrayInsert allows the user to specify where the item have to be placed

  &reftitle.examples;

   mysql_xdevapi\CollectionModify::arrayAppend example


<?php

//Assuming $coll is a valid Collection object

//For each document with a `job` like Programmatore or Cantante, add an additional
//job: 'Volontario'
$coll->modify("job in ('Programmatore', 'Cantante')")->arrayAppend('job', 'Volontario')->execute();

?>


